Here's the Fibonacci sequence using recursion:

```python
def fibonacci(n):
    if n <= 0:
        return 0
    elif n == 1:
        return 1
    return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2)
```

This follows the mathematical definition: F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2).

Note: This naive implementation has exponential time complexity O(2^n). For better performance, consider memoization or iteration.
